Dr.Shambulinga is a very nice and friendly doctor. He understands the problem and provides clarity on the treatment.
I was little scared for dental procedures due to past experiences but the doctor made me very comfortable, explaining every step and making sure I didn't feel anxious.
I got my fillings, cap replacement and teeth cleaning.All done with utmost care. The clinic is clean , hygienic and the pricing is also fair. Dr Veena mam is also very pleasant and welcoming.My overall experience is Great.I am so happy that I found this clinic and would highly recommend. ** ** *** **** ******* * **** **** ****

More than a doctor, he is a well-wisher. Guided me exactly and accurately what to do. Honestly speaking he took care of me like his own son. Much friendly, trustworthy, simply you can rely on him. I'm pretty sure he wit never ever misguide anyone. To be said in short the best dentist I ever met in my life time.
Not even a single negative feedback I could think of him. Genuine doctor, only phrase comes in my mind is "Being simple is the best thing, being modest is the next best thing", Dr.Shambulinga is both simple and modest.

Note: the previous question I had given wait time to be improved, infact there has to be an option like none the above. He is perfect in what he is.

Guys, any dental issue. Just close your eyes and think of Dr.Shambulinga, he is the best option. You may find good doctors out in market. But he is the best of all.

Thanks a lot for your valuable time to treat me sir. Hope we stay as friends for ever 🙏

survey_response.review_text:
I visited the doctor for my father's teeth issues. He have had just a few left and those as well were in very bad condition. The doctor immediately recommended tooth extraction and full denture replacement. 
My father's had very high blood pressure issues. The doctor said it's fine to extract the teeth even when informed. He did not inform me about payment details in advance even when asked. Tooth extraction was done by some another doctor and not by Dr. Shambulinga. The new doctor after extracting 2 of the 5 teeth said the BP is way too high and we shall first consult a specialist for that. The specialist doctor eventually asked not to do any dental procedure as the BP is way too high.
Post this I went to the doctor and asked him to refund the money except for the tooth extraction part. The doctor refunded 5k out of 10k (advance). He charged 2.5k per tooth extraction!!* *** ******** **** ** *** **** ** *** ******* ** ******* *** ****** On confrontation he gave insignificant reasons.

I had my Mom's RCT done here and we were more than satisfied with the treatment without much pain. More than me, my Mom was scared but the way Dr. Shambhulinga explained the problem and made her comfortable was exceptional. I would definitely recommend him for all dental related problems, he will guide you completely and would advice what is good. 
Thank you so much doc for your support, courage and patience to make understand a patient the root cause of a problem in a polite and friendly way.

This was my first visit to a dentist in Bangalore and I purposely kept it discreet that I have a dentist family member. As expected, the dentist didnt even check with us if we needed the cleaning or filling or something else!
The problem was in right tooth and in his excitement he also cleaned the left tooth.
Now what did he clean on the left side???
It was a cavity filling done earlier. So if its a permanent cavity filling, why did he remove it?? Just to fill up again so that he could bill more!!!

The end of story is, we went with one problem of right side, now we are sitting with pain on both sides!!
Biggest problem with this doctor is - he doesn't listen *** **** ******* **** ** ****** ********
